Package com.oracle.javafx.scenebuilder.api.util

Interface FxmlController

All Known Implementing Classes:
AboutWindowController, AbstractFxmlController, AbstractFxmlPanelController, AbstractFxmlPopupController, AbstractFxmlViewController, AbstractFxmlWindowController, AbstractHierarchyPanelController, AbstractModalDialog, AlertDialog, CertificateManagerWindowController, ContentPanelController, CssPanelController, DebugMenuWindowController, DockWindowController, DocumentPanelController, DocumentWindowController, DummyWindowController, ErrorDialog, ExtensionImportWindowController, ExtensionLibraryWindowController, HierarchyPanelController, HierarchyTreeViewController, ImageImportWindowController, ImageJarAnalysisReportController, ImageLibraryPanelController, ImportProgressDialogController, ImportWindowController, InfoPanelController, InspectorPanelController, JarAnalysisReportController, JavaFxFeaturesWindowController, LibraryDialogController, LibraryPanelController, LogViewerController, MavenDialogController, MessageBarController, MessagePanelController, PreferencesWindowController, RegistrationWindowController, RepositoryDialogController, RepositoryManagerController, SearchController, SearchMavenDialogController, SelectionBarController, SkeletonWindowController, SourceViewWindowController, TemplatesBaseWindowController, TemplatesWindowController, TextViewDialog, WelcomeDialogWindowController
public interface FxmlController
This interface must be used in conjunction with Spring Dependency injection framework. When implementing this interface you're delegating the fxml loading task to the Spring context using getFxmlURL() and getResources() as parameters. You will then be notified of the result with calls to setRoot(Parent) and controllerDidLoadFxml() May be used with Component annotation or any spring annotation making the implementing class a spring bean
Author:
ptreilhes

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    void controllerDidLoadFxml()
    This method is automatically called by SceneBuilderBeanFactory.FxmlControllerBeanPostProcessor.postProcessAfterInitialization(Object, String) after a successful call to FXMLLoader.load() using getFxmlURL() and getResources() as parameters and a successful call to setRoot(Parent) It notify the controller that all loading activities have ended successfully
    URL getFxmlURL()
    Must return a valid URL to an Fxml file.
    ResourceBundle getResources()
    May return a valid ResourceBundle containing all the necessary keys to translate every i18n expression ("%xxx.xxx") contained in the fxml file provided by getFxmlURL()

  • Method Details

    • getFxmlURL

      @NonNull URL getFxmlURL()
      Must return a valid URL to an Fxml file. The instance implementing this interface will be used as a javafx controller for this fxml file. Which means any fields or methods annotated with @FXML will be binded using this fxml
      Returns:
      the url to the fxml that must be binded to this controller

    • getResources

      ResourceBundle getResources()
      May return a valid ResourceBundle containing all the necessary keys to translate every i18n expression ("%xxx.xxx") contained in the fxml file provided by getFxmlURL()
      Returns:

    • setRoot

      void setRoot​(javafx.scene.Parent root)
      This method is automatically called by SceneBuilderBeanFactory.FxmlControllerBeanPostProcessor.postProcessAfterInitialization(Object, String) after a successful call to FXMLLoader.load() using getFxmlURL() and getResources() as parameters. The return value of FXMLLoader.load() will be used as parameter for this function
      Parameters:
      root - the Parent root of the provided fxml file
